article.headline: The Citadel 74, Furman 69
article.story: GREENVILLE, S.C. -- Zach Urbanus scored nine of The Citadel's 12 points in overtime as the Bulldogs rallied to defeat Furman 74-69 on Thursday night. Cameron Wells scored 22 points for the Bulldogs (8-9, 3-3 Southern Conference) and Urbanus finished with 20 to keep the Paladins (2-12, 0-5) winless in league play. Furman, which had won the last four games and 13 of the previous 15 in the 189-game series, took a 32-24 halftime lead. Wells scored 17 points in the second half on 8-for-10 shooting to even the game at 62 at the end of regulation. That's when Urbanus took over. He had a 3-pointer, a layup and hit four foul shots -- the last pair with 3 seconds left -- to seal the win. Furman was 1-for-7 from the field in overtime. Justin Dehm and Jordan Miller led the Paladins with 17 points apiece. The Bulldogs won the battle of the boards 38-16.
